<h2>SPARQL</h2>

<p>SPARQL, which stands for SPARQL Protocol and RDF Query Language, is a complex querying language and protocol for querying and manipulating RDF (Resource Description Framework) data. RDF facilitates data merging, serves as a model for exchanging data online and stands as a crucial component of the Semantic Web (W3C, 2014). In SPARQL, the structure of the data is outlined in a WHERE clause that is based on graph patterns (Van Hooland & Verborgh, 2014). It is created to handle various data types, so it retrieves information from inconsistent data stored in various formats and locations. The SPARQL standard is developed by the W3C and it enables users and developers to focus on their queries rather than the structure of the database (Ontotext, 2023).</p>

